      <h1>How Annuities Work: Types, Pros, Cons, and Who Should Buy One</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Annuities are one of the most misunderstood financial products in the retirement planning world. Insurance companies sell over 300 billion dollars worth of annuities every year in the United States, yet many buyers do not fully understand the fees, surrender schedules, or tax implications before signing a contract. This guide breaks down how annuities actually work, the major types available, the costs you need to watch for, and the specific situations where an annuity makes sense — and where it does not.</p>
    </header>

